# Record architecture decisions

Date: 2021-04-28

## Status

Proposed

## Context

We need to accept tickets and response back success to customer

## Decision

We will write to No SQL DB, so that we can handle the large number of request.
## Consequences

See Michael Nygard's article, linked above. For a lightweight ADR toolset, see Nat Pryce's [adr-tools](https://github.com/npryce/adr-tools).

**Positive:**  Solves the problem related to spike in request.

**Negative:** If any

**Risks:** If any

**Bonus Features:** If any
